<emphasis box="[374,478,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Falobase</emphasis>
with superior border with deep concavity. 
<emphasis box="[968,1173,1251,1275]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Spiculum gastrale</emphasis>
with two small acuminate protuberances and inner area strongly bulged, extending the prominences outward (Fig. 
<number box="[1236,1268,1286,1310]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" value="34.0">34</number>
). 
<emphasis box="[1291,1435,1286,1310]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Median lobe</emphasis>
robust, dorsal-hook; 
<emphasis box="[383,448,1324,1347]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">uncus</emphasis>
short and moderately robust (
<figureCitation box="[784,869,1322,1346]" captionStart="FIGURES 37 – 44" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1975,1998]" captionTargetBox="[242,1345,220,1931]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[225,1359,193,1957]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES 37 – 44. Aedeagus, lateral view: 37. E. bosqi: (a) aedeagus, (dt) dorsal tooth, (h) hook; 38. Epicauta clericalis; 39. E. excavata; 40. E. grammica 41. E. leopardina; 42. E. luteolineata; 43. E. monachica; 44. E. semivittata." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/203654/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">
Fig. 
<number box="[837,869,1322,1346]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38" value="42.0">42</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,350,1778]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,481,1358,1383]" pageId="17" pageNumber="38">Intra-specific variation.</emphasis>
Variation in body length and tonality color of pubescence occurs. This species has a wide range of size. The pubescence varies between brown and light brown.
</paragraph>
